                <h1>Understanding Security Clearance Levels: Key Insights</h1>
                <p>Security clearance levels are essential for safeguarding sensitive information. They range from Confidential to Top Secret, determining the degree of access individuals have based on their trustworthiness and the nature of their work. These levels are crucial for national security, privacy protection, and are governed by federal regulations.</p>
